      "name": "Hemolysis index comparison against FDA experimental benchmark",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against published FDA experimental measurements across 5 operating points (flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM). Mean absolute relative error of 18.4% observed across all operating points. Uncertainty in experimental measurements is discussed qualitatively; batch-to-batch variability in blood analog fluid and pump manufacturing tolerances contribute to scatter in the reference data. No formal UQ artifact is linked to this result as aleatory variability in experimental conditions was characterized only in narrative form.",
