      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) evaluation across operating envelope",
      "description": "RH index computed for all 5 flow-speed combinations relative to predicate device baseline. RH < 1 for 4 of 5 operating points; worst-case point at 2 L/min and 3500 RPM yields RH = 0.94, confirming device meets acceptance criterion. Natural variability in patient hematocrit, plasma viscosity, and red blood cell fragility are acknowledged in the discussion section as sources of aleatory uncertainty but are not formally propagated through the model or linked to a quantification artifact.",
